commit.message:
Recognize EX_DLLCHARACTERISTICS debug type

Merely updates the two-way dict, but more work is likely needed to
properly support this.

https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/debug/pe-format#extended-dll-characteristics

Recognize the IMAGE_DEBUG_TYPE_REPRO debug type

The presence of this flag indicates that the PE binary was built with
`/Brepro` by the MSVC linker. See:
https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/debug/pe-format#debug-type

Closes https://github.com/erocarrera/pefile/issues/228

commit.message:
Make maximum exported symbol limit configurable

Many interesting binaries export more than 8k symbols.
Preparing for a small release with the latest speed ups

Merging changes from Google

Merging contributed changes which speed up ordinal and exports parsing.
Updated test blob and setup
Synced README to the changes of README.md
Implemented the changes suggested in #218

Improved handling of CV_INFO_PDB70 format

This addresses #252 improving the formatting of the GUID.
The change also adds minor tweaks to the PR #257 and removes the redundant "h" suffix from some hex numbers which already have the "0x" prefix.
